    Route::get('/projects/{project}/activity', [ActivityLogController::class, 'forProject'])->name('activity.project');
    Route::get('/tasks/{task}/activity', [ActivityLogController::class, 'forTask'])->name('activity.task');
```

### Step 5: Run all tests
```bash
php artisan test --filter=ActivityLogTest
```
Expected: All 13 tests PASS.

### Step 6: Run full test suite
```bash
php artisan test
```
Expected: All tests pass, no regressions.

**Do NOT commit. Just leave files as-is.**

## Key Notes
- `forTask()` uses `authorize('update', $task)` — TaskPolicy has no 'view' method; 'update' verifies ownership. This is intentional.
- `$log->user?->name ?? 'Sistema'` handles both null user_id (seeder logs) and deleted users.
- `created_at` is cast to `datetime` on ActivityLog model so `->format()` works.

